cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.SE

The paper discusses the design and implementation of a network infrastructure for interplanetary communication, which involves challenges related to network architecture, physical infrastructure, and technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of various technologies such as artificial intelligence (AI) and software engineering (SE) to handle deep space communication, which suggests the possibility of categorizing it under cs.AI and cs.SE. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of coding and modulation techniques to improve the reliability of communication, which suggests the possibility of categorizing it under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of maintaining a network infrastructure in a highly dynamic and unpredictable environment, which suggests the possibility of categorizing it under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
